  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Education for Children from the Plateau, Eastern DRC</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Many children living in the war-affected area of the Democratic Republic of Congo do not have the opportunity to go to schools with proper facilities, reading materials or even exercise books. School buildings are ramshackled and teachers are not always adequately trained and often go for long periods without even being paid. Children In Crisis supports works in a particularly neglected and isolated region training teachers to improve their teaching methods. They distribute school kits with essential educational materials, such as books and pens, and work with parents and communities using theatre, drama and songs to encourage them to send their children to school and to value education. As a result of the project, thousands more children enrol and stay in school, get better marks in their exams, and have more confidence in their ability to learn.</narrative>
  </description>
